  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my purpose and-- and goal was to reconstitute, revive, and-- and-- and assure the continuity and the permanence of Jews and Judaism.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was driven, virtually, by a-- a kind of inner compulsion about this because this I could perceive as the only purpose of survival.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] If Judaism and Jews were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] not to survive, then what was the purpose of my survival?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the one sure way to assure the survival of the Jewish people was the-- the Zionist goal, which to me not only meant the reestablishment of-- of Jewish sovereignty, but also the reconstitution of and-- and the recreation of-- of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I-- I-- you know, I had a-- an-- an everlasting, lifelong goal in my life, which, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you know, served as the purpose and-- and-- of my survival.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had no difficulty with it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I have, therefore, spent [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] nearly 50 years of my life in-- as a Jewish public servant in various organizations-- first for some 13, 14 years with the Zionist Organization of America and then for a similar number of years with B'nai B'rith.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And eventually, I spent a couple of years as the executive vice president of the America-Israel Cultural Foundation and then went to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to Israel as the founding director of the-- the Public Affairs Department of the new university that was being built in the Negev, which eventually became Ben-Gurion University.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And subsequently, eventually I came to work for the Canadian Associates of Ben-Gurion University, for about 16 or 17 years, in Montreal as-- as the national director of the Associates.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course that, shall I say, was the-- the-- largely the intellectual side of my survival.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
